; SERIES return truncation + LET placeholders: a bound query over
; differential data generates a top-down checker procedure built from
; RETURN-true/RETURN-false sequences; two differential sources give the
; checker multiple all-paths-return sub-regions before the fallback
; RETURN (indirect-return truncation), and check bodies that collapse to
; no-ops leave empty placeholder LETs.

#message a(i32 X) @differential.
#message b(i32 X) @differential.
#local t(i32 X).
#query chk(bound i32 X).
#query all(free i32 X).

t(X) : a(X).
t(X) : b(X).
chk(X) : t(X).
all(X) : t(X).
